main event: Seven yellow or orange objects were observed in formation at high speed over Gibson City, Illinois.
interesting points: The objects were sighted moving at an estimated speed of up to 3000 mph,The sighting occurred on a clear night with initial altitude reported at 60,000 ft,The objects appeared as lights only and were not identifiable as any known aircraft,The sighting lasted for approximately 15 minutes and included no optical aids for observation,The report suggested the possibility of a satellite being in the area at the time of the sighting.
witness description: Mr. and Mrs. of Gibson City, Illinois
